cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the automatic recognition of communicative functions in dialogues, which is a task related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a hierarchical network with cascading outputs, which is a common approach in deep learning, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category. The use of transfer learning and mapping processes to improve performance suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category. The paper deals with a specific dataset (DialogBank), which suggests that cs.SD (Sound) could be a relevant category. Finally, the paper deals with the interpretation of dialogues, which could be related to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
